"/> Many do just that. I suggest you not generalize. Bally's is known for
having membership contracts with a lot of fine print, but no one is ever
placed in a situation where a gun is held to their head to have them
sign a contract. I used to be a member of Bally's for many years and I
never had a problem and their gym in my area was fantastic. I only quit
because my employer opened up a gym right across from my office and, so
I simply didn't renew my membership at Bally's when my contract expired.
This is no different than any other situation where signing a contract
is involved. The consumer is always well advised to read the contract
carefully before signing.

