The last time I had a club membership, they started out with a really
good deep-water class once a week and a &quot;social hour&quot; water aerobics class
several times a week, so it was almost worth the $100/month I was paying. When
they cancelled the deep-water class due to lack of interest*, I quit. I don't
want to socialize, I want to work out. Apparently I'm alone in that.

* Water aerobics has a terrible reputation for being classes for &quot;fat, lazy,
or old people&quot;, which simply shouldn't be true. So I couldn't figure out why
the deep-water class, which was a kick-butt workout, was scorned by everyone
